            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract ">Upriver (Chiliwack dialect) Halkomelem language material recorded with speaker Dr. Elizabeth Herrling in Chiliwack, B.C., in 2004 and 2005. The majority of the recordings consists of elicited words, phrases, and sentences. Also includes three autobiographical texts and a description of pit lamping and fishing activities. Recorded by Jason Brown and others, occasionally identified on the recordings, including Strang Brown, Maliol Harris, James Thompson, and Martina WIltschko.</abstract>
